 800,000 deaths annually By Sola Ogundipe Nigeria contributes the highest number to global pneumonia child deaths! Pneumonia – a preventable disease – kills more children globally than any other infection!! These were the screaming headlines on this year’s World Pneumonia Day – 12th November, following the release of the latest data on the global burden of the biggest killer of little children- pneumonia. The new analysis by UNICEF and partners revealed that pneumonia claimed the lives of more than 800,000 children under the age of five globally in 2018, or one child every 39 seconds, even as Nigeria recorded the highest-burden with an estimated 162,000 deaths or 443 deaths per day (18 deaths every hour), READ ALSO: Nigeria records highest global pneumonia deaths in 2018 Four other countries – India (127,000), Pakistan (58,000), the Democratic Republic of Congo (40,000) and Ethiopia (32,000), along with Nigeria were responsible for more than half of child pneumonia deaths. Continue reading Global alarm as pneumonia kills 1 child every 39 seconds at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard At last, there is a ray of light at the end of the tunnel for Pneumonia patients as the journal, Science Advances, recently published a breakthrough in the production of a new vaccine, which has the propensity to deal with 72 forms of Streptococcus Pneumoniae , which cause pneumonia in… November 8, 2017 In "News" With an estimated 162,000 children that reportedly died of pneumonia in Nigeria in 2018, the country has been said to have the highest number of pneumonia deaths globally. The post Nigeria tops global pneumonia mortality with 162,000 deaths yearly appeared first on The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World… November 12, 2019 In "News" A new report by the United Nations Children Fund (UNICEF) on Tuesday says Nigeria records the highest global deaths of pneumonia in 2018. Continue reading Nigeria records highest global pneumonia deaths in 2018 at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard N